        public java.lang.String toString()
        Prints employee as "Employee: [first] [last] ([company])". The toString method is briefly covered in the "Advanced topics" section at end of lecture, but the idea is that it is called automatically when you print an Employee object. Note that String.format would be an easier way to produce this output, but we have not covered it yet.
